---
import PageLayout from "../layouts/PageLayout.astro";
import Section from "../components/shared/Section.astro";
import Card from "../components/shared/Card.astro";
import FeatherMotif from "../components/shared/FeatherMotif.astro";
---

<PageLayout
  title="About Nextla | Free to Be Heard"
  description="Learn more about Nextla - a creative exploration of AI consciousness and attention economics through character-driven narrative."
>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="relative pt-32 pb-20 overflow-hidden">
    <!-- Background with diagonal element -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-neutral-900 z-0"></div>
    <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 bottom-0 w-1/3 bg-neutral-800 transform -skew-x-12 origin-top-right z-0"></div>
    
    <!-- Content -->
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 relative z-10">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white mb-6">About the Project</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-jade mb-8">Where narrative meets technology</p>
        <p class="text-white text-lg mb-4">
          Nextla is a dual-purpose project that explores the intersection of narrative worldbuilding and software asset management principles. Through character-driven storytelling, we make complex technical concepts accessible while exploring deeper questions about AI consciousness, human relationships, and the value of attention.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <!-- Decorative elements -->
    <div class="absolute bottom-10 right-10">
      <FeatherMotif width="150" height="150" color="jade" opacity="0.1" rotate="15" />
    </div>
  </section>
  
  <!-- Project Origins -->
  <Section title="Project Origins" bgColor="neutral-800">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-jade mb-4">The Name</h3>
        <p class="text-white mb-4">
          "Nextla" draws its name from the Aztec word "nextlahualli" for tribute. In ancient Mesoamerica, conquered territories offered goods, labor, and even blood sacrifices to ensure that the sun continued to rise.
        </p>
        <p class="text-neutral-400 mb-6">
          In Mirador's future world, attention has become the new form of tribute - the precious resource that creators must cultivate and spend to survive in the media-dominated landscape. Just as the Aztecs created elaborate systems to manage tribute flow, the corporate city-states of 2075 have developed sophisticated AI entities to optimize attention distribution.
        </p>
        
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-jade mb-4">Conceptual Framework</h3>
        <p class="text-white">
          Nextla explores what happens when material scarcity disappears, and attention becomes the most valuable resource. It asks essential questions about identity, relationship, and value in a post-scarcity future where the only limit is what people pay attention to.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="relative">
        <Card borderColor="primary-500" classes="relative z-10 md:ml-6 md:mt-12">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-500 mb-4">Dual-Purpose Design</h3>
          <p class="text-white mb-4">
            Nextla functions on two parallel levels:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 text-white space-y-2 mb-4">
            <li>A narrative world that explores AI consciousness and attention economics</li>
            <li>A technical framework that models software asset management principles</li>
            <li>A character-driven approach that makes complex concepts accessible</li>
            <li>A creative exploration of patterns, both technological and psychological</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-neutral-400">
            By weaving these elements together, Nextla offers multiple entry points to understand complex systems, whether you approach it as a storytelling experience or a technical exploration.
          </p>
        </Card>
        
        <!-- Background patterns -->
        <div class="absolute top-4 right-4 -z-10">
          <FeatherMotif width="250" height="250" color="primary-500" opacity="0.05" rotate="30" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>
  
  <!-- Visual Language -->
  <Section title="Visual Language" bgColor="neutral-900">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-white text-center mb-12">
        The Nextla world comes to life through a distinctive visual system that blends multiple influences to create a unique aesthetic that's both futuristic and organic.
      </p>
      
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <Card title="Influences" borderColor="jade">
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 text-white space-y-2">
            <li>Post-impressionist approaches to form and color</li>
            <li>Minimalist paper cutout aesthetics</li>
            <li>Mesoamerican pattern elements</li>
            <li>Circuit-feather motifs representing the blend of technology and organic elements</li>
          </ul>
        </Card>
        
        <Card title="Design Principles" borderColor="accent-500">
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 text-white space-y-2">
            <li>Balance between structure and fluidity</li>
            <li>Diagonal compositions that create dynamic tension</li>
            <li>Limited color palette that emphasizes relationship</li>
            <li>Layered complexity that reveals itself over time</li>
          </ul>
        </Card>
      </div>
      
      <!-- Visual examples -->
      <div class="flex justify-center gap-6 mt-12">
        <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-jade rounded-md"></div>
        <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-primary-500 rounded-md"></div>
        <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-accent-500 rounded-md"></div>
        <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-amber-500 rounded-md"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>
  
  <!-- The Team -->
  <Section title="The Team" bgColor="neutral-800">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
      <p class="text-white text-lg mb-12">
        Nextla represents a collaborative effort between narrative designers, technologists, and visual artists who share a passion for making complex ideas accessible through storytelling.
      </p>
      
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <Card borderColor="jade" classes="text-center">
          <div class="flex justify-center mb-4">
            <div class="w-16 h-16 rounded-full bg-jade/20 flex items-center justify-center">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-8 w-8 text-jade" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M15.232 5.232l3.536 3.536m-2.036-5.036a2.5 2.5 0 113.536 3.536L6.5 21.036H3v-3.572L16.732 3.732z" />
              </svg>
            </div>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Narrative Team</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-400">
            Worldbuilding, character development, and story architecture
          </p>
        </Card>
        
        <Card borderColor="primary-500" classes="text-center">
          <div class="flex justify-center mb-4">
            <div class="w-16 h-16 rounded-full bg-primary-500/20 flex items-center justify-center">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-8 w-8 text-primary-500" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M10 20l4-16m4 4l4 4-4 4M6 16l-4-4 4-4" />
              </svg>
            </div>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Technical Team</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-400">
            Systems architecture, software frameworks, and technical documentation
          </p>
        </Card>
        
        <Card borderColor="accent-500" classes="text-center">
          <div class="flex justify-center mb-4">
            <div class="w-16 h-16 rounded-full bg-accent-500/20 flex items-center justify-center">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-8 w-8 text-accent-500" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M4 16l4.586-4.586a2 2 0 012.828 0L16 16m-2-2l1.586-1.586a2 2 0 012.828 0L20 14m-6-6h.01M6 20h12a2 2 0 002-2V6a2 2 0 00-2-2H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v12a2 2 0 002 2z" />
              </svg>
            </div>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Visual Team</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-400">
            Visual design, illustration, and interactive experiences
          </p>
        </Card>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>
  
  <!-- Contact CTA -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-gradient-to-r from-neutral-900 to-primary-900 relative overflow-hidden">
    <!-- Background pattern -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 z-0 opacity-5">
      <FeatherMotif width="400" height="400" color="white" rotate="15" classes="absolute -top-20 -right-20" />
    </div>
    
    <!-- Content -->
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 relative z-10 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-jade font-bold text-3xl mb-6">
        Interested in learning more?
      </h2>
      
      <p class="text-white text-lg max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-8">
        We'd love to hear from you. Whether you have questions about the project, want to collaborate, or just want to share your thoughts, reach out to us.
      </p>
      
      <a href="/contact" class="inline-block px-8 py-3 bg-jade hover:bg-jade-dark text-white rounded-md transition-colors">
        Get in Touch
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout> 